2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-left-trial-short-seller-doj-securities-fraud-citron-research-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Left%3C%2Fa%3E's%20ongoing%20securities%20fraud%20trial%2C%20the%20defense%20has%20repeatedly%20returned%20to%20a%20simple%20question%3Cstrong%3E%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECan't%20people%20disagree%20about%20stocks%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECitron%20Research%20founder%20Left%2C%20known%20for%20his%20bets%20on%20GameStop%20and%20frequent%20appearances%20on%20financial%20shows%2C%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20manipulating%20the%20market%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshort-seller-andrew-left-fraud-trial-kicks-off-jury-selection-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeceiving%20retail%20investors%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethrough%20misleading%20statements.%20Prosecutors%20allege%20Left%20said%20one%20thing%20about%20over%2020%20stocks%20and%20then%20traded%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction%2C%20making%20over%20%2420%20million%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20into%20the%20trial%2C%20it's%20becoming%20clearer%20how%20the%20defense%20plans%20to%20handle%20the%20prosecution's%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20prosecutors%20have%20focused%20on%20the%20stocks%20of%20two%20companies%20they%20say%20Left%20tweeted%20about%20and%20then%20traded%20on%3A%20the%20social%20media%20site%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%20and%20Cronos%20Group%2C%20a%20cannabis%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20have%20highlighted%20the%20negative%20reports%20Left%20issued%20about%20those%20companies%20and%20called%20stock%20analysts%20who%20disagreed%20with%20his%20takes%20to%20testify.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20defense%20argued%20that%20disagreement%20over%20a%20stock%20does%20not%20necessarily%20constitute%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeft%20issued%20a%20report%20in%20December%202018%20titled%20%26quot%3BTwitter%20has%20become%20the%20Harvey%20Weinstein%20of%20social%20media%26quot%3B%20that%20cited%20an%20Amnesty%20International%20study%20documenting%20issues%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%20had%3C%2Fa%3E%20regarding%20abusive%20content%20against%20women.%20He%20set%20a%20target%20stock%20price%20of%20%2420%2C%20well%20below%20its%20then-trading%20price%20of%20around%20%2430.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Anmuth%2C%20an%20internet%20analyst%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-track-software-engineers-ai-use-dashboards-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20JPMorgan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20testified%20Wednesday%20that%20he%20covered%20Twitter%20at%20the%20time%20and%20disagreed%20with%20Left's%20report.%20He%20said%20issues%20with%20hate%20speech%20on%20Twitter%20were%20well%20known%2C%20and%20the%20company%20had%20taken%20steps%20to%20address%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20pressed%20Anmuth%20on%20whether%20disagreements%20among%20analysts%20necessarily%20meant%20something%20nefarious%20was%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFair%20to%20say%20when%20you%20and%20any%20other%20analyst%20disagree%2C%20that%20might%20just%20be%20a%20difference%20of%20opinion%2C%20correct%3F%26quot%3B%20Adam%20Fee%2C%20Left's%20lawyer%2C%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnmuth%20agreed%2C%20and%20a%20bit%20later%2C%20Fee%20raised%20the%20point%20again%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20would%20agree%20generally%20that%20reasonable%20people%20can%20disagree%20about%20how%20information%20in%20the%20market%20might%20impact%20stock%20prices%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20can%20disagree%2C%26quot%3B%20Anmuth%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20third%20occasion%2C%20Fee%20asked%20Anmuth%2C%20whose%20Twitter%20price%20target%20was%20%2445%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-left-trial-securities-fraud-defense-sec-market-manipulation-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECitron%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whether%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20people%26quot%3B%20could%20disagree%20about%20price%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20pattern%20played%20out%20during%20the%20earlier%20testimony%20on%20Wednesday%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20Martin%20Landry%2C%20an%20analyst%20who%20was%20covering%20Cronos%20Group%20in%20August%202018%2C%20when%20Left%20tweeted%20a%20negative%20report%20about%20the%20company.%20Landry%20testified%20that%20he%20wrote%20a%20rebuttal%20report%20at%20the%20time%20that%20said%20some%20of%20Left's%20allegations%20about%20Cronos%20appeared%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bunfounded%20and%20biased.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20cross-examination%2C%20Fee%20noted%20that%20Landry%20did%20not%20accuse%20Left%20of%20sharing%20false%20information%2C%20but%20that%20he%20disagreed%20with%20the%20importance%20Left%20placed%20on%20certain%20facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFee%20also%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20said%20'buy%2C'%20another%20said%20'sell%2C'%20the%20guy%20who%20said%20sell%20wasn't%20committing%20fraud%2C%20correct%3F%26quot%3B%20Landry%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20more%2C%20he%20asked%20Landry%20if%20he%20agreed%20that%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20can%20reasonably%20disagree%20about%20the%20value%20of%20a%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20line%20of%20questioning%20seemed%20to%20align%20with%20the%20central%20argument%20Left's%20defense%20led%20with%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshort-seller-andrew-left-trial-opening-statements-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopening%20statements%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%3A%20%26quot%3BHe%20tells%20the%20public%20what%20he%20believes%20%E2%80%94%20the%20truth%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20he%20trades%20on%20the%20truth%20to%20make%20a%20profit.%20It's%20not%20fraud.%20That's%20trading.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeft's%20lawyers%20also%20leaned%20on%20his%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%20In%20their%20opening%20stat