C%20proposal%20to%20reduce%20reporting%20requirements%20for%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20popular%20Reddit%20community%20believes%20the%20plan%20would%20be%20a%20blow%20to%20retail%20traders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20said%20that%20WallStreetBets%20members%20rely%20on%20regular%20earnings%20updates%20for%20vital%20information.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERetail%20traders%20on%20WallStreetBets%20are%20not%20on%20board%20with%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission's%20plan%20to%20dial%20back%20reporting%20requirement%20for%20public%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fwallstreetbets%2Fcomments%2F1t4sukk%2Fsec_considering_giving_companies_option_to_report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebashing%20the%20idea%20in%20discussions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20popular%20investing%20forum%2C%20a%20public%20comment%20submitted%20to%20the%20SEC%20by%20users%20of%20the%20subreddit%20on%20Wednesday%20hit%20back%20at%20the%20proposal%20for%20firms%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsec-quarterly-reporting-plan-earnings-stock-market-transparency-investors-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereport%20financial%20results%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20twice%20per%20year%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20against%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20comment%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20proposal%20rests%20on%20the%20theory%20that%20quarterly%20reporting%20causes%20short-termism%20among%20corporate%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fcomments%2FS7-2026-15%2Fs7202615-775527-2368994.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20comment%3C%2Fa%3E%20stated.%20%26quot%3BWhatever%20the%20merits%20of%20that%20argument%20as%20applied%20to%20the%20C-suite%2C%20it%20has%20the%20relationship%20to%20retail%20investors%20exactly%20backwards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%2C%20who%20did%20not%20reveal%20their%20names%20in%20the%20letter%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fcomments%2FS7-2026-15%2Fs7202615-775527-2368994.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%20highlighted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20importance%20of%2010-Qs%2C%20not%20just%20as%20a%20means%20of%20transparency%20and%20information%2C%20but%20as%20a%20tool%20that%20helps%20bridge%20the%20gap%20between%20retail%20and%20institutional%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Reddit%20community%20is%20well%20known%20for%20its%20slogan%3A%20%26quot%3BLike%204chan%20found%20a%20Bloomberg%20Terminal%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20edgy%20internet%20forum%20known%20for%20its%20memes.%20But%20as%20the%20letter%20noted%2C%20most%20retail%20traders%20don't%20actually%20have%20access%20to%20a%20pricey%20Bloomberg%20terminal%20%2C%20which%20provides%20institutional%20investors%20with%20troves%20of%20information%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichael-bloomberg-terminal-wall-street-data-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethousands%20of%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20retail%20traders%20on%20WallStreetBets%20and%20elsewhere%20often%20depend%20on%20public%20info%20such%20as%20quarterly%2010-Qs%20to%20understand%20market%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstitutional%20investors%20have%20expert%20networks%2C%20channel%20checks%2C%20alternative%20data%2C%20satellite%20imagery%20of%20retailer%20parking%20lots%2C%20credit%20card%20panel%20data%2C%20and%20direct%20management%20access%20through%20conferences%20and%20one-on-one%20meetings%20that%20cost%20more%20than%20most%20of%20our%20portfolios.%20We%20have%20the%2010-Q.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comment%20goes%20on%20to%20say%20that%20many%20WallStreetBets%20members%20learned%20about%20investing%20by%20buying%20stocks%2C%20watching%20them%20fall%2C%20and%20turning%20to%20the%20next%20earnings%20report%20to%20learn%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20a%20stupid%20order%20of%20operations%20and%20we%20acknowledge%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20author%20added.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20also%20the%20entire%20mechanism%20by%20which%20a%20generation%20of%20retail%20investors%20taught%20itself%20to%20read%20financial%20statements%2C%20and%20the%20Commission%20is%20now%20proposing%20to%20cut%20that%20mechanism%20in%20half.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20noted%20that%20if%20the%20SEC's%20proposal%20moves%20forward%20and%20quarterly%2010-Q%20requirements%20are%20eliminated%2C%20retail%20investors%20will%20be%20at%20a%20significant%20disadvantage%20relative%20to%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20authors%20acknowledged%20the%20SEC's%20argument%20that%20companies%20will%20face%20less%20financial%20pressure%20if%20they%20are%20required%20to%20post%20fewer%20earnings%20disclosures.%20Kunal%20Kapoor%2C%20CEO%20of%20market%20research%20firm%20Morningstar%2C%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsec-quarterly-earnings-reporting-proposal-morningstar-ceo-kunal-kapoor-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshares%20this%20view%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Bets%20forum%20members%20behind%20the%20letter%20maintain%20that%20any%20savings%20would%20not%20pose%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20companies%20they%20are%20concerned%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20entire%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20files%20a%2010-Q%20every%20quarter%2C%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20at%20an%20all-time%20high.%20If%20quarterly%20reporting%20is%20crushing%20American%20capitalism%2C%20American%20capitalism%20is%20hiding%20it%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Frules-regulations%2Fpublic-comments%2Fs7-2026-15%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20SEC%20has%20received%20dozens%20of%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20of%20them%20coming%20out%20strongly%20against%20the%20agency's%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoubling%20the%20time%20between%20disclosures%20is%20a%20gift-wrapped%20invitation%20for%20corporate%20malfeasance%2C%20fraud%2C%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20accounting%20shell%20games%20that%20wiped%20out%20shareholders%20at%20Enron%20and%20WorldCom%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20anonymous%20comment%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20ain't%20broke%2C%20so%20don't%20try%20to%20fix%20it.%20This%20lack%20of%20reporting%20would%20create%20a%20gulf%20between%20the%20information%20the%20institutional%20investor%20would%20have%20vis-a-vis%20the%20retail%20investor.%20Please%20reject%20this%20solution%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20comment%20submitted%20by%20an%20advisor%20at%20Geneos%20Wealth%20Management%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWallStreetBets%20moderator%20Noor%20Al%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20in%20his%20view%2C%20the%20letter's%20message%20is%20consistent%20with%20what%20the%20community%20stands%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20an%20age%20of%20unprecedented%20technology%2C%20markets%20should%20trend%20to%20lower%20information%20asymmetry.%20We%20should%20see%20more%20frequent%2C%20not%20less%2C%20corporate%20updates%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20the%20administrative%20costs%20are%20a%20burden%2C%20but%20it%20is%20worth%20the%20price%20to%20remain%20the%20greatest%20place%20in%20the%20world%20to%20invest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WallStreetBets%20comment%20goes%20on%20to%20note%20that%20the%20proposed%20reporting%20changes%20would%20severely%20undermine%20the%201934%20Securities%20Exchange%20Act%2C%20created%20to%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsecurities-and-exchange-commission%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elevel%20the%20playing%20field%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20investors%20following%20the%20stock%20market%20crash%20of%201929.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Commission%20has%20spent%2090%20years%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20people%20like%20us%20to%20participate%20in%20public%20markets%20on%20something%20approaching%20fair%20terms%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20stated.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20asking%20the%20Commission%20not%20to%20spend%20this%20rulemaking%20making%20it%20harder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwallstreetbets-sec-quarterly-earnings-proposal-requirement-reddit-retail-traders-investing-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778703318000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04d3a3ecd7cc1332baee68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwallstreetbets-sec-quarterly-earnings-proposal-requirement-reddit-retail-traders-investing-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20comment%20submitted%20by%20the%20investing%20forum%20bashed%20the%20SEC's%20plan%2C%20noting%20the%20importance%20of%20quarterly%20reports%20to%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20for%20retail%20traders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22See%20the%20list%20of%2017%20routes%20that%20lost%20all%20air%20service%20after%20Spirit%20collapsed%2C%20with%201%20airport%20completely%20abandoned%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223523%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20empty%20spirit%20desk%20at%20Latrobe%20airport.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04b12f58810e27922ad4b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222349%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELatrobe%20Airport%20outside%20Pittsburgh%20was%20left%20without%20air%20service%20after%20Spirit's%20collapse.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Merriman%2FFor%20The%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EData%20shows%2017%20nonstop%20flight%20routes%20lost%20all%20service%20after%20Spirit%20folded.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20tiny%20airport%20outside%20Pittsburgh%20was%20completely%20abandoned.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERoughly%20half%20of%20the%20now-empty%20routes%20Spirit%20left%20behind%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20other%20budget%20airlines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspirit-airlines-collapses-shuts-down-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpirit%20Airlines'%20collapse%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20travelers%20without%20nonstop%20options%20on%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20routes%20across%20the%20US%20and%20Latin%20America%2C%20but%20competitors%20are%20already%20moving%20to%20fill%20much%20of%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20now-defunct%20budget%20airline%20abruptly%20ceased%20flying%20in%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20May%202%20after%20years%20of%20unrecoverable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-smart-people-say-possible-spirit-airlines-trump-bailout-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elosses%20driven%20by%20rising%20labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20changing%20traveler%20habits%2C%20and%20then%20the%20recent%20surge%20in%20fuel%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Spirit%20held%20only%20about%201.7%25%20of%20the%20US%20market%20share%20when%20it%20fell%2C%20per%20Cirium%2C%20its%20absence%20still%20matters.%20A%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20using%20data%20from%20Cirium%20and%20Raymond%20James%20found%20that%2017%20routes%20and%20one%20airport%20were%20abandoned%20after%20Spirit's%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20hardest%20hit%20were%20Atlantic%20City%20International%20Airport%20in%20New%20Jersey%20and%20Arnold%20Palmer%20Regional%20Airport%20in%20Latrobe%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20about%2030%20miles%20outside%20Pittsburgh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20aviation%20analytics%20company%20Cirium%20shows%20Atlantic%20City%20lost%20roughly%20half%20its%20flights%2C%20with%20budget%20carriers%20Breeze%20and%20Allegiant%20still%20flying%20to%20the%20airport%3B%20the%20Pennsylvania%20airport%20lost%20all%20its%20airline%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20places%20like%20Atlantic%20City%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-rise-and-fall-of-spirit-airlines-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpirit%20pressured%20fares%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20airlines%20facing%20less%20competition%20now%20will%20likely%20raise%20ticket%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20routes%20with%20only%20one%20competitor%20have%20stepped%20up%20from%20eight%20to%2063%20(2%25%20to%2019%25%20of%20total)%20while%20those%20with%20four%20or%20more%20stepped%20down%20from%20203%20to%2052%20(60%25%20to%2015%25%20of%20total)%2C%26quot%3B%20RJ%20analyst%20Savanthi%20Syth%20said%20in%20a%20note%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20Spirit's%20now-empty%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20list%20of%20now-empty%20routes.%20Eight%20are%20expected%20to%20regain%20nonstop%20service%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20Atlantic%20City%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWest%20Palm%20Beach%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOrlando%20(MCO)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMyrtle%20Beach%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFort%20Myers%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20Fort%20Lauderdale%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EArmenia%2C%20Colombia%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBarranquilla%2C%20Colombia%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBelize%20City%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECali%2C%20Colombia%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKey%20West%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELima%2C%20Peru%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESan%20Antonio%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESt.%20Thomas%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESt.%20Croix%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EComayagua%2C%20Honduras%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20Latrobe%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMyrtle%20Beach%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOrlando%20(MCO)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20Orlando%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMedell%C3%ADn%2C%20Colombia%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tiny%20Labrobe%20airport%20was%20exclusively%20served%20by%20Spirit%20for%2015%20years%20and%20was%20even%20building%20a%20second%20gate%20to%20support%20growth%20before%20it%20was%20left%20vacant.%20Cirium%20shows%20the%20last%20time%20the%20airport%20had%20no%20airline%20service%20was%20in%20early%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Workers%20at%20Latrobe%20pack%20up%20the%20airport.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04ac9258810e27922ad493%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmployees%20at%20Latrobe%20airport%20pack%20up%20after%20Spirit%20ceased%20operations.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Merriman%2FFor%20The%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d67e4a36-57cb-4b38-9762-35e789b79188%5C%22%3EMany%20abandoned%20Spirit%20routes%20will%20be%20rescued%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERoughly%20half%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspirit-airlines-collapse-employees-jobs-workers-flight-attendant-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpirit's%20abandoned%3C%2Fa%3E%20routes%20will%20not%20remain%20empty%20for%20long%2C%20as%20airlines%20including%20Breeze%2C%20Allegiant%2C%20and%20JetBlue%20move%20in.%20Carriers%20like%20United%2C%20Frontier%2C%20Delta%2C%20and%20American%20have%20also%20added%20flights%20in%20response%20to%20Spirit's%20demise%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20replacements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtlantic%20City%20will%20see%20relief%20starting%20May%2021%2C%20when%20Allegiant%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lesser-known%20budget%20leisure%20carrier%20headquartered%20in%20Las%20Vegas%20%E2%80%94%20starts%20its%20new%20nonstop%20route%20to%20Myrtle%20Beach.%20The%20route%20was%20planned%20before%20Spirit%20shut%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflying-breeze-airways-first-time-kids-cheap-flights-family-review-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBreeze%2C%20a%20newer%20low-cost%20carrier%3C%2Fa%3E%20focused%20on%20niche%20point-to-point%20flying%2C%20will%20also%20begin%20serving%20the%20beach%20town%20from%20Atlantic%20City%20in%20October%2C%20announcing%20its%20plans%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20Spirit's%20collapse.%20It's%20also%20taking%20over%20Spirit's%20former%20routes%20from%20the%20resort%20city%20to%20Orlando%2C%20West%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20and%20Fort%20Myers%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllegiant%20already%20travels%20to%20Orlando%20from%20Atlantic%20City%2C%20but%20not%20to%20the%20main%20Orlando%20International%20Airport%20(MCO)%2C%20where%20Spirit%20flew.%20It%20flies%20instead%20to%20Orlando%20Sanford%20International%20Airport%20(SFB)%2C%20the%20city's%20secondary%20airport%2C%20but%20it's%20farther%20from%20downtown%20and%20attractions%20like%20Walt%20Disney%20World.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Raymond%20James%20considers%20routes%20to%20nearby%20competing%20airports%20as%20still%20served%2C%20Business%20Insider%20counted%20them%20separately%20because%20airport%20swaps%20can%20affect%20traveler%20convenience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFort%20Lauderdale%20%E2%80%94%20once%20Spirit's%20biggest%20Florida%20hub%20%E2%80%94%20will%20see%20a%20surge%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjetblue-fort-lauderdale-spirit-airlines-routes-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereplacement%20flying%20from%20JetBlue%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20airline%20announced%20its%20addition%20of%2011%20new%20routes%20from%20the%20city%2C%20including%20service%20to%20Cali%20and%20Barranquilla%2C%20two%20destinations%20left%20abandoned%20by%20Spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Spirit's%20former%20nonstop%20flights%20from%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20to%20St.%20Thomas%3B%20St.%20Croix%3B%20Comayagua%2C%20Honduras%3B%20Key%20West%3B%20Belize%3B%20Lima%3B%20and%20Armenia%20will%20remain%20vacant%20for%20now.%20Southwest%20will%20run%20a%20handful%20of%20flights%20to%20San%20Antonio%20in%20late%202026%2C%20but%20the%20route%20will%20otherwise%20be%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETravelers%20can%20still%20reach%20those%20cities%20nonstop%20from%20nearby%20Miami%20%E2%80%94%20about%2026%20miles%20from%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20%E2%80%94%20via%20American%20Airlines%2C%20Chile's%20LATAM%20Airlines%2C%20and%20the%20South%20American%20budget%20carrier%20SKY%20Airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Orlando's%20Medell%C3%ADn%20service%20is%20set%20to%20return%2C%20though%20not%20as%20a%20direct%20replacement%20for%20Spirit.%20Colombian%20carrier%20Avianca%20is%20resuming%20its%20previously%20planned%20seasonal%20summer%20flights%20in%20June%2C%20becoming%20the%20route's%20only%20airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20only%20one%20carrier%20now%20on%20dozens%20of%20more%20routes%2C%20fares%20are%20likely%20to%20rise%20soon.%20A%20Business%20Insider%20study%20in%20April%2C%20using%20Cirium%20data%2C%20found%20that%20routes%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairfare-data-ticket-prices-could-jump-14-if-spirit-collapses-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpirit%20exited%20saw%20an%20average%20ticket%20price%20jump%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2014%25.%20Some%20rose%20by%20over%20%24100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20any%20airline%20leaves%20a%20market%2C%20it%20results%20in%20a%20drop%20in%20the%20supply%20of%20seats%2C%26quot%3B%20Mike%20Arnot%2C%20an%20airline%20industry%20consultant%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat%20generally%20means%20that%20airfare%20will%20increase%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20much%20matter%20which%20airline%20departs%20a%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-list-routes-airport-abandoned-after-spirit-shut-down-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778702521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04b13d58810e27922ad4b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-list-routes-airport-abandoned-after-spirit-shut-down-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Spirit%20Airlines%20was%20small%20compared%20to%20its%20legacy%20counterparts%2C%20but%20its%20demise%20has%20left%20over%20a%20dozen%20routes%20and%20one%20airport%20without%20air%20service%20at%20all.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22trains%40businessinsider.com%20(Taylor%20Rains)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A95%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LinkedIn's%20layoffs%20will%20come%20with%20operational%20changes%2C%20memo%20shows%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225076%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22LinkedIn%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04a7f195396a3b6e417fe7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223626%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELinkedIn%3Cp%3EIllustration%20by%20Klaudia%20Radecka%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELinkedIn%20is%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-the-internal-memo-from-linkedins-ceo-on-layoffs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaying%20off%20employees%20and%20%26quot%3Bscaling%20back%26quot%3B%20some%20investments%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20layoffs%2C%20the%20company%20is%20making%20changes%20to%20its%20product%20operations%2C%20according%20to%20a%20memo.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20changes%20are%20aimed%20at%20creating%20more%20focused%20teams%20and%20leveraging%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20layoffs%20are%20coming%20with%20changes%20to%20some%20of%20the%20company's%20operations%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20memo%20from%20its%20chief%20product%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20on%20Wednesday%20announced%20in%20an%20internal%20memo%20from%20CEO%20Daniel%20Shapero%20that%20it%20would%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-the-internal-memo-from-linkedins-ceo-on-layoffs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elay%20off%20employees%20and%20scale%20back%20some%20investments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20separate%20email%20from%20Hari%20Srinivasan%2C%20who%20became%20%26quot%3Bchief%20product%20officer%20of%20the%20LinkedIn%20Ecosystem%26quot%3B%20in%20March%2C%20outlines%20three%20shifts%20the%20company%20is%20planning%20amid%20the%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20fastest%20moving%20teams%20are%20focused%2C%20have%20fewer%20layers%2C%20and%20leverage%20AI%20to%20move%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Srinivasan%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20changes%20we're%20making%20across%20our%20Product%20orgs%20are%20based%20on%20creating%20more%20agile%20teams%20in%20this%20model.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20parent%20company%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20has%20similarly%20been%20making%20changes%20to%20remove%20management%20layers%20and%20create%20more%20focused%20teams.%20Microsoft%20CFO%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosofts-cfo-intensity-internal-earnings-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmy%20Hood%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20sent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finternal-microsoft-cfo-memo-touts-increased-pace-tighter-teams-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20internal%20memo%20to%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlighting%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20pace%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btighter%2C%20more%20accountable%20squads.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20its%20plan%20to%20get%20teams%20to%20move%20faster%2C%20LinkedIn%20is%20also%20changing%20how%20design%20and%20research%20support%20work%2C%20according%20to%20the%20memo.%20The%20company%20is%20centralizing%20its%20user%20experience%20design%20resources%20so%20product%20teams%20can%20handle%20routine%20work%20and%20expert%20researchers%20can%20focus%20on%20more%20complex%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20also%20plans%20to%20change%20how%20it%20produces%20learning%20content%20on%20the%20site.%20The%20company%20says%20it%20is%20switching%20from%20producing%20large-scale%20original%20content%20in-house%20to%20a%20model%20in%20which%20instructors%20can%20produce%20and%20monetize%20their%20teaching%20directly%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20LinkedIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Flinkedin-introduces-creator-monetization-threads-welcomes-g9zle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20allowing%20creators%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20monetize%20their%20content%20on%20the%20network%20through%20video%2C%20but%20this%20appears%20to%20be%20expanding%20revenue%20opportunities%20for%20instructors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20model%20%26quot%3Bis%20no%20longer%20the%20best%20model%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20what%20learners%20want%20or%20the%20more%20cost%20effective%20way%20to%20create%20all%20our%20content%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20new%20model%20will%20allow%20%26quot%3Binstructors%20%5Bto%5D%20build%20a%20voice%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20across%20multiple%20tools%2C%20and%20license%20and%20monetize%20their%20teachings%20directly%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%26quot%3B%20Srinivasan%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20will%20allow%20the%20in-house%20team%20to%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bhigh-impact%2C%20differentiated%20learning%20experiences%20that%20are%20best%20built%20internally%26quot%3B%20and%20rely%20on%20content-creating%20instructors%20to%20keep%20LinkedIn%20fresh%20with%20timely%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20part%20of%20our%20regular%20business%20planning%2C%20we've%20implemented%20organizational%20changes%20to%20best%20position%20ourselves%20for%20future%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20LinkedIn%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fbcf3aa-a22f-4e10-b450-1e0165af604f%5C%22%3ERead%20the%20memo%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BTeam%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20you%20saw%20in%20Dan's%20note%2C%20we're%20making%20changes%20across%20Linkedin%20to%20simplify%20how%20work%20gets%20done%20and%20focus%20product%20investments.%20This%20includes%20the%20difficult%20decision%20to%20reduce%20some%20of%20Product.%20I%20wanted%20to%20follow%20up%20with%20why%20we%20are%20doing%20it%2C%20where%20we%20will%20work%20differently%2C%20and%20what%20comes%20next.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhy%20we%20are%20making%20changes%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELinkedin%20is%20an%20incredible%20platform.%20Our%20mission%20to%20help%20people%20connect%20to%20opportunity%20has%20never%20been%20more%20relevant.%20Our%20engaged%20community%2C%20unique%20data%20and%20diversified%20business%20me%20also%20position%20us%20well%20in%20a%20changing%20world%20of%20Al%20%26amp%3B%20technology.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20two%20shifts%20are%20changing%20how%20we%20need%20to%20operate.%20First%2C%20we%20now%20have%20tools%20that%20let%20us%20ship%20faster%20-%20and%20we%20need%20to%20ensure%20we%20have%20an%20organizational%20structure%20that%20allow%20harness%20them.%20Second%2C%20our%20infrastructure%20costs%20will%20grow%20as%20we%20deliver%20more%20intelligent%20products%20-%20requiring%20hard%20prioritization%20and%20tradeoffs.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhere%20we%20work%20differently%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThese%20shifts%20require%20changes%20to%20what%20%26amp%3B%20how%20we%20build%20for%20our%20members%20and%20customers.%20So%20we're%20evolving%20our%20operating%20model%20in%20the%20following%20ways%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EAcross%20our%20Product%20orgs%3A%20Our%20fastest%20moving%20teams%20are%20focused%2C%20have%20fewer%20layers%2C%20and%20leverage%20AI%20to%20move%20quickly.%20The%20changes%20we're%20making%20across%20our%20Product%20orgs%20are%20based%20on%20creating%20more%20agile%20teams%20in%20this%20model.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EArchitecture%3A%20As%20teams%20build%20faster%2C%20insights%20need%20to%20scale%20across%20the%20product%20ecosystem%20quicker.%20To%20support%20this%2C%20we're%20evolving%20our%20operating%20model%20across%20Content%20Design%20and%20User%20Research%20from%20embedded%20teams%20to%20a%20shared%20service%3B%20teams%20can%20utilize%20off%20the%20shelf%20UX%20resources%20themselves%2C%20while%20expert%20researchers%20focus%20on%20our%20most%20complex%20work.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EContent%3A%20Our%20current%20learning%20content%20model%20is%20built%20around%20large-scale%20original%20production%2C%20but%20that%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20best%20model%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20what%20learners%20want%20or%20the%20more%20cost%20effective%20way%20to%20create%20all%20our%20content.%20We%20are%20shifting%20to%20a%20new%20model%20where%20instructors%20can%20build%20a%20voice%20on%20Linkedin%2C%20across%20multiple%20tools%2C%20and%20license%20and%20monetize%20their%20teachings%20directly%20on%20Linkedin.%20This%20allows%20us%20to%20give%20learners%20what%20they%20want%20%E2%80%94%20timely%20content%20across%20multiple%20formats%20%E2%80%94%20and%20focus%20our%20in%20house%20content%20creation%20on%20high-impact%2C%20differentiated%20learning%20experiences%20that%20are%20best%20built%20internally.%20As%20part%20of%20this%20change%2C%20and%20to%20align%20our%20workplace%20footprint%20to%20our%20business%20needs%2C%20we%20will%20be%20closing%20our%20physical%20office%20in%20Graz%2C%20Austria.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20comes%20next%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThose%20directly%20impacted%2C%20or%20proposed%20to%20be%20impacted%20in%20EMEA%20%26amp%3B%20APAC%20consultative%20countries%2C%20will%20receive%20a%20calendar%20invitation%20within%20the%20next%20hour%20titled%20%26quot%3BAttendance%20Required%3A%20Product%20Organizational%20Updates%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20meetings%20starting%20today%2C%20May%2013%20for%20EMEA%20and%20NAMER%2C%20followed%20by%20APAC%20on%20Thursday%2C%20May%2014%20local%20time.%20If%20you%20do%20not%20receive%20this%20exact%20invitation%2C%20your%20role%20is%20not%20impacted%20or%20proposed%20to%20be%20impacted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETo%20those%20who%20are%20leaving%2C%20thank%20you.%20Your%20hard%20work%20and%20dedication%20got%20us%20to%20where%20we%20are%3B%20a%20billion%20people%20have%20gotten%20jobs%2C%20learned%20skills%2C%20stayed%20informed%20and%20more%20because%20of%20your%20contributions.%20I'm%20thankful%20for%20everything%20you%20have%20given%20us%2C%20and%20we%20are%20committed%20to%20supporting%20you%20through%20this%20transition.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMoments%20like%20this%20are%20very%20difficult%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20also%20remind%20us%20why%20our%20mission%20to%20connect%20people%20to%20economic%20opportunity%20matters.%20Please%20take%20the%20time%20you%20need%20to%20process%20this%20and%20support%20one%20another...%20and%20thank%20you%20for%20your%20continued%20focus%2C%20care%2C%20and%20commitment%20to%20building%20products%20that%20matter.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHari%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBCC%3A%20Product%20All%3A%20Product%20Functional%20Partners%3B%20Eng%20LT%3B%20GBO%20LT%2C%20Marketing%20LT%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20Ashley%20Stewart%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aastewart%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eastewart%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%2B1-425-344-8242.%20Contact%20Alex%20Bitter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20808-854-4501.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%